OL,4,CHead Coach
OL,6,FAfter a spell with FC Porto's junior
OL,7,Fside, he was given the reins at
OL,8,FPortuguese sides Sanjoanense and
OL,9,FEspinho before he returned to Porto's
OL,10,Fyouth side.
OL,12,FIn 2010, he became the assistant
OL,13,Fmanager to Andre Villas-Boas, when he
OL,14,Fleft for the Chelsea job, Pereria was
OL,15,Fpromoted to number one.
OL,17,FHe guided his side to the league title
OL,18,Fin the 2011/12 and 2012/13 seasons. As
OL,19,Fwell as picking up both Portuguese
OL,20,Fsuper cups.
